<h1>Surveys</h1>
<p>Every semester the SRC sends out an email to all enrolled students inviting them to join Student Voice. Student Voice is a group of over 3,000 students who agree to take&nbsp; surveys of university concerns. The Student Representative Council uses these survey results to guide SRC representatives in their respective administrative councils.</p>
<h1>Volunteer Sessions</h1>
<p>SRC volunteers meet for two hours&nbsp;each week. Student Voice volunteers use an online database program to sort, summarize, and discuss students' responses to open-ended survey questions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Click <a href="http://www.byui.edu/student-support/volunteer/volunteer-opportunities/src">here</a> to sign up to be a Student Voice Representatives!</p>
<h1>The Power of Data</h1>
<p>The student voice empowers the SRC to take a more active role in representing students. As student representatives identify widespread student concerns, they use statistics from the student voice to show the degree to which certain problems are affecting students.&nbsp;Upon identification of these&nbsp;problems&nbsp;they propose solutions which administration takes into consideration.</p>
